2026-04-21 01:36:35 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 6 – n port'] hypothesis_explanation='The only anomaly found in the otherwise correctly wired series chain is that Control Input Cable (+) 6 has its negative side (n port) disconnected and floating. This floating conductor corresponds to the negative return for the pair that should feed Control Module 6. As a result, the main series path for the 0 V line is open at module 6: the positive line is continuous, but the negative line is interrupted. This open circuit prevents current from flowing through the chain, so none of the downstream control-module LEDs nor the load lamp can energize, even though the PSU LED is on and all switches are ON. Reconnecting the n port of Control Input Cable (+) 6 into the series return path (to its proper mating negative terminal between modules 5 and 6) should restore continuity and allow the system to operate normally.'
